Nancy Allen, 72, has aged gracefully since beginning her Hollywood career in the 1970s, with her first major role coming in 1976's Carrie. As RoboCop airs on TV this evening, Express.co.uk looks back at Nancy and her big moments as she started her successful career. The actress stunned in the portraits dated 1978, taken in Los Angeles, California. She posed with her hand on her face covering her modesty as she posed topless. Nancy also had wet hair, adding a racy element to the unearthed snaps. Throughout her career she received several accolades including a Golden Globe Award nomination and three Saturn Award nominations. You can watch Nancy in RoboCop at 9pm tonight on ITV4